[start section id="20112"]

I reviewed everything with the patient and her daughter.  I agree with Ms. Rubalcava's assessment and recommendations.  The benefit of chemotherapy is small in-patient's with T3, N0 tumors.  The patient has some neurologic deficit from her stroke, and she lives at-home with her husband who has also had a stroke.  In view of this, I would not recommend any adjuvant chemotherapy.  I have explained this to the daughter and to the patient.  They are both in agreement.  The patient will be following-up locally with her physicians and not planning to return here.  We will not see her again unless requested.

[end section id="20112"]

