[start section id="20103"]

I have reviewed and confirm the history and physical examination as per Jesse Rubalcava's note of September 14, 2010, and agree with her evaluation.  Briefly, this is a lady with an underlying history of a stroke in June 2010 leading to gait changes and 12th nerve palsy, type-2 diabetes, and hypertension.  She developed weakness and was found to be anemic.  A cecal mass was found, and she was referred to Colonial Manor Home and Hospital where she had a proctocolectomy because of multiple polyps.  Her mismatch repair status is negative.  She is currently recovering.

[end section id="20103"]

